##Nmap Scan Report
Overview
This project shows how to use Nmap to scan a target, find open ports, detect services, check the OS, and gather security information.
Target used: demo.testfire.net

Commands Used
Ping Scan: nmap -sn target

TCP SYN Scan: nmap -sS target

Version Detection: nmap -sV target

OS Detection: nmap -O target

Full Port Scan: nmap -p- target

Key Results
Target is live.

Several open ports with services identified.

Service versions and OS were detected.

Full scan confirmed no missed ports.

Conclusion
Nmap is useful for checking network devices, services, and security gaps. Always scan only systems you have permission to test.
